Listen on BandcampWhen it comes to electro-pop, Canada has a great tradition, ranging from TransX to Mitsou to Fanny Bloom. Montreal-based Scarlatine (nom de plume of Judith Brodeur-Rowe) paints a very moody picture, with several shades of black and grey. No wonder one of her tracks is called Noir. But Navire is the one to dive in to, building like a big wave to give you chills. • More from Filles Sourires • New music from Australia: Milwaukee Banks – Pluto Bounce• New music from Russia: Fourth Way – Aleph